steps.description:
[FIX: resource_leak] Fix the diagnostics listener lifecycle in Editor.tsx. Replace the current pattern:
```
createDiagnosticsListener(cb).then(unlisten => { unlistenDiagnostics = unlisten; });
```
with a cancellation-safe pattern using a `cancelled` flag:
```
let diagnosticsListenerCancelled = false;
createDiagnosticsListener(cb).then(unlisten => {
  if (diagnosticsListenerCancelled) {
    unlisten(); // Component already unmounted, tear down immediately
  } else {
    unlistenDiagnostics = unlisten;
  }
});
```
In `onCleanup`, set `diagnosticsListenerCancelled = true` before calling `unlistenDiagnostics?.()`. This ensures that if the component unmounts before the Promise resolves, the unlisten function is called as soon as it becomes available, preventing the Tauri event listener from leaking.
